doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    meta(charset="UTF-8")
    meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
    link(rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com")
    link(rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin)
    link(href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Aldrich&family=Exo+2:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet")
    link(href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons"
      rel="stylesheet")
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/style.css")
    title Scott Casey | Kurohyou Studios
  body
    header
      h1 Scott Casey
      h2 Digital Conversion Specialist
    nav
      ul
        li
          a(href="#about-header") About me
        li
          a(href="#project-header") Work
        li
          a(href="#contact-header") Contact Me!
    .hero
    main
      section(aria-labelledby="about-header")
        .sectionHeader.h2#about-header 
          h2 Scott Casey
          img.profile-pic(alt="Scott Casey and Koda" src="assets/images/profile.jpg")
        div
          p I got started in web development through converting tabletop RPGs to virtual tabletops. I have created products for some of the biggest names in the tabletop and VTT spaces including Roll20, Paizo, and Pinnacle Entertainment. I am passionate about bringing the fun of tabletop gaming to the virtual space so that everyone can play and socialize no matter the distance between them. Part of this passion includes making sure that the products I create are as accessible as possible so that anyone, regardless of ability, can enjoy a game night with friends and family.
          p I am currently working on improving my skills to become a full stack developer through the #[a(href="https://bootcamps.continue.utah.edu/coding/?utm_source=university-course-page") University of Utah Full Stack Coding Bootcamp].
        h3.sectionHeader Kurohyou Studios
        div
          p Kurohyou Studios was founded in 2020 as a way for me to organize my various projects on Roll20. The studio's #[a(href='https://www.patreon.com/kurohyoustudios?fan_landing=true') patreon page] is where my work on Roll20 character sheets and tools can be supported by the community. It's also where I post updates on my sheet creation tutorial and release notices for the various tools and frameworks that I have created.
      section(aria-labelledby="project-header")
        h2.sectionHeader#project-header Work
        //- Add project elements here
        .flex.flex-center.brick-mortar
          each obj,index in cardContent
            div(class=`project-container project-container--${obj.cardType}`)
              a(href=obj.siteLink || obj.repositoryLink).card
                img(alt=obj.imageAlt src=`assets/images/${obj.image}`)
                h3 #{obj.Name}
                - category = obj.Categories || [];
                - languages = obj.Languages || [];
                span.categories #{obj.Categories}
                span.languages #{obj.Languages}
      //- Descriptive Content will be displayed eventually
        each obj,index in cardContent
          .target-section(id=`section-${index}`)
            h3.sectionHeader #{obj.Name}
            each content in obj.content
              p #{content}
      section(aria-labelledby="contact-header")
        h2.sectionHeader#contact-header Contact me
        .flex.flex-space-evenly
          +socialIcons
